<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: is it possible to add a DS li-ion accumulator to DMG Gam]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10022&amp;p=111046#p111046"><![CDATA[
Basically, you want to integrate a Li-on or Li-po cell battery and a charging circuit inside? <br /><br />A workaround solution is to use the DS as a charger, making an external link from inside the game boy to allow temporary connection to the DS's battery contacts. <br /><br />I did something like this a few years ago with a GB Pocket and a GBA SP...<br />That's what the RJ-11 jack is for. <br /><img src="http://bibin.gg8.se/image/xtr3.JPG" alt="Image" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5314">mikejmoffitt</a> — Mon Apr 15, 2013 3:29 pm</p><hr />
